annotationA: Henna (Hn) is a tryptophan phenylalanine hydroxylase. Hn is a dual function enzyme: it hydroxylates both phenylalanine to generate tyrosine, as well as tryptophan to generate the precursor for peripheral (non-neuronal) serotonin. Hn is also involved in pteridine synthesis
annotationB: Dihydrofolate reductase; By interacting with vestigial (vg), may control genes involved in DNA replication
